“As to how long this war will last, we are not the ones who’ll decide. It used to depend on President Truman, and it will depend on President Eisenhower or whoever to become the next US president, it’s up to them. No matter how long they want this war to last, we’ll never yield. We’ll fight until we completely triumph!”

RT @HuXijin_GT: I saw someone claiming on social media that Hamas military commander Mohammed Deif has connections with China. That’s total…

result.text:
I saw someone claiming on social media that Hamas military commander Mohammed Deif has connections with China. That’s totally bullshit and a very vicious rumor. China only recognizes the Palestinian Authority led by President Mahmoud Abbas, and has no connections with Hamas.

Mohammed Deif’s whereabouts are so mysterious that the outside world cannot even confirm what he looks like. Information about him in Western media is also scarce. Besides, those Western media outlets that often radically attack China have never made allegations of “China supporting Hamas.” Some individuals with ulterior motives fabricate connections between Mohammed Deif and China -- because people basically know nothing about him, and they thought they can make it up at will. But fabricating lies via social media won’t succeed. Those who are shamed in the end will be the rumormongers themselves.
